"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715549","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-04-18T12:09:44.847Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715549/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715549/answer","PQ 70164 v.02.pdf","PQ 70164 v.02.pdf","UKSA Response to PQ70164","UKSA Response to PQ70164","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715549/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-30","Self-employed: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people are currently registered as self-employed in (a) Coventry South constituency, (b) the city of Coventry and (c) the West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","70164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715550","Women and Equalities","false","2017-04-24","<p>The new fund will support projects celebrating the centenary of the Representation of the People Act 1918, which extended voting rights to women for the first time. We hope the fund will help build a legacy for the future by educating young people about this important milestone and inspiring women to get more involved in politics at all levels.</p><p> </p><p>Details of how people can apply for funding, what criteria will need to be met and when the scheme will start will be announced in due course.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-04-24T16:23:42.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715550/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715550/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715550/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-03-30","Voting Rights: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, when she plans to announce further details of the £5 million funding to be made available to women's groups to celebrate 100 years of voting rights for women announced in the Spring Budget 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","69992"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715551","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-20","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring we have the very best people appointed to our public bodies and that the boards of public bodies reflect society as a whole.</p><p> </p><p>We encourage applications from candidates with a diverse range of skills and backgrounds and have recently made a number of improvements to the appointments process, which are aimed at making public appointments accessible to the widest possible group of people.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-04-20T10:12:11.097Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715551/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715551/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715551/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-30","Business Appointments Advisory Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will make it his policy to encourage the Advisory Committee on Business Appointments to diversify its membership beyond the current required senior (a) military, (b) diplomatic and (c) business experience.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","70000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715552","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>We have taken the opportunity to review the returns, and have updated the records on GOV.UK to ensure full transparency on meetings with senior media executives.</p><p> </p><p>This was simply an administrative oversight by diary officials. This was an informal occasion in a social setting, and not a formal government meeting, it was not recorded on the return by accident.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","70012","2017-04-18T12:14:51.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715552/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715552/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715552/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-30","Viscount Rothermere","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 30 March 2017 to Question 62917, whether any other such meetings have been omitted from the official records on gov.uk.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","70011"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715553","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>We have taken the opportunity to review the returns, and have updated the records on GOV.UK to ensure full transparency on meetings with senior media executives.</p><p> </p><p>This was simply an administrative oversight by diary officials. This was an informal occasion in a social setting, and not a formal government meeting, it was not recorded on the return by accident.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","70011","2017-04-18T12:14:51.553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715553/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715553/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715553/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-30","Viscount Rothermere","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 30 March 2017 to Question 62917, for what reason the meeting of 11 February between David Cameron and Lord Rothermere was omitted from the original record on gov.uk.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","70012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715554","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>Civil Servants have to ability to work flexibly across government sites where there is a business need to do so. The issuing of all passes is controlled by the local Departmental Security teams who follow strict procedures and protocols. Information on the number of people holding security passes for other government departments who are granted access to the Cabinet Office premises is not centrally recorded.</p><p> </p><p>My department has issued a total of 12,065 building access passes since 2010.</p><p> </p><p>My department has 2,506 active passes.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","70034 ; 70055","2017-04-18T15:03:47.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715554/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715554/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715554/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-30","Cabinet Office: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many security passes giving access to his Department's premises are currently valid.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","70017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715555","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Treasury does not collect data relating to bank branch closures.</p><p> </p><p>Treasury Ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery. Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p><p> </p><p>The Chancellor of the Exchequer and other Treasury Ministers receive numerous representations concerning the impact of bank branch closures, which are taken into consideration in the development of Government policy. However, decisions on the opening and closing of individual bank branches are taken by the management of each bank on a commercial basis without intervention from Government. For this reason, the Government welcomed the industry-wide Access to Banking Protocol and Professor Griggs’ independent ‘one year on’ review, published last November.</p><p> </p><p>While banks and building societies need to balance customer interests, market competition, and other commercial factors when considering their strategy, the Government is pleased to see that the industry is committing to further improvements to protect those affected by branch closures.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","70128 ; 70129 ; 70130 ; 70155 ; 70187 ; 70188 ; 70205","2017-04-18T13:37:17.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715555/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715555/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715555/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-30","Royal Bank of Scotland: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many local bank branches of the Royal Bank of Scotland have closed in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","69995"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715556","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-24","<p>HM Treasury receives a wide range of representations from stakeholders, including from the alcohol industry.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-04-24T11:04:59.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715556/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715556/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715556/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-30","Whisky: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations his Department has received from Scottish whiskey producers on  the increase in excise duties on spirits in the Spring Budget 2017.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","69989"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715557","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-24","<p>The restriction of finance costs tax relief for landlords does not mean that landlords will be taxed on their income. Landlords will still be able to deduct other costs incurred in letting out a property when calculating their taxable profits, and will receive tax relief on their finance costs at the basic rate of tax.</p><p> </p><p>Only 1 in 5 landlords are expected to pay more tax as a result of this change. Given the small proportion of the housing market affected by this, the Government does not expect a significant impact on rent levels or the supply of rented accommodation. The Office for Budget Responsibility also expect the impact on the housing market will be small.</p><p> </p><p>Landlords do not provide the location of their let properties on their tax return.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-04-24T11:33:34.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715557/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715557/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715557/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-30","Rented Housing: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of taxing landlords on their income rather than profit on the supply of affordable rented accommodation in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","69991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715558","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-24","<p>There are tax incentives already available for businesses which support not-for-profit and charitable organisations. Qualifying donations receive corporation tax relief, and sponsorship payments are tax deductible as business expenses.</p><p> </p><p>Charities whose main purpose is to provide air ambulance services have been included in the VAT refund scheme since April 2014, meaning they can claim refunds of VAT incurred on their non-business activities.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","69975","2017-04-24T11:58:28.357Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715558/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715558/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715558/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-30","Aviation: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to incentivise corporate sponsorship of not-for-profit flight training and flying schools.","false","Biography information for Sir Roger Gale","North Thanet","Sir Roger Gale","69974"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715559","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-24","<p>There are tax incentives already available for businesses which support not-for-profit and charitable organisations. Qualifying donations receive corporation tax relief, and sponsorship payments are tax deductible as business expenses.</p><p> </p><p>Charities whose main purpose is to provide air ambulance services have been included in the VAT refund scheme since April 2014, meaning they can claim refunds of VAT incurred on their non-business activities.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","69974","2017-04-24T11:58:28.42Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715559/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715559/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715559/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-30","Charities: Sponsorship","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will take steps to incentivise corporate sponsorship of air ambulances, civil air patrols and other not-for-profit and charitable organisations.","false","Biography information for Sir Roger Gale","North Thanet","Sir Roger Gale","69975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715560","Home Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>In response to part (a) of the question, City of London Police (CoLP) is the National Lead Force for Fraud, who also oversee the Action Fraud and National Fraud Intelligence Bureau (NFIB) Services. Action Fraud is the national reporting centre for all frauds and cyber crimes, whilst the NFIB performs analysis to link crimes, to then create crime packages, which are then sent to the most appropriate local police force to consider for investigation, where viable lines of inquiry exist. As part of CoLP’s role as national lead force, they also take on, or assist forces, in investigating the most serious and complex frauds. The National Crime Agency and Serious Fraud Office also play a vital role in investigating the most high-end, cross border economic crimes.</p><p> </p><p>One of the priorities of the Joint Fraud Taskforce (a collaborative response to fraud which brings together Government, law enforcement and the financial sector) is to improve the law enforcement response at the local, regional and national levels. This work is focused on improving the end-to-end policing system for fraud.</p><p> </p><p>In response to part (b) of the question, Special Grant Funding is available if a Police Force faces a significant and unexpected event which could threaten the financial stability of the Force. Police and Crime Commissioners can apply for Special Grant funding when the additional costs incurred are greater than one per cent of the PCC’s budget.</p><p> </p><p>The Thames Valley PCC has made an application for Special Grant for the costs of Operation Hornet (the investigation into large scale fraud perpetrated from within Halifax and Bank of Scotland). This has been referred to HMIC for their views, after which Ministers will take a decision on whether to provide Special Grant funding.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2017-04-18T16:49:14.367Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715560/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715560/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715560/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-30","Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the recent case of fraud committed at the Reading branch of HBOS, what plans she has to establish a (a) National Fraud Investigation Service and (b) central fund to reimburse local police forces for the costs of investigating such cases.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","69910"
