"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715710","Home Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Office for National Statistics release annual figures on breakdown of Civil Servants across all Government Departments.</p><p>www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/datasets/civilservicestatisticsdatasummarytool</p><p>For 2016, there were 26,540 FTE under the Home Office.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-18T16:04:38.077Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715710/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715710/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715710/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-30","Home Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people are currently employed by her Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","70088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715711","Home Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>All individuals in possession of a valid Common Civil Service Pass may gain access to the Department, subject to them holding the correct level of national security vetting. The Home Office does not hold data on how many passes other departments issue.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-04-18T15:59:21.72Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715711/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715711/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715711/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-30","Home Office: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people holding security passes for other Government Departments are granted access to her Department's premises with that pass, by Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","70065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715712","Home Office","false","2017-04-21","<p>This Government takes seriously the issue of online illegal content on social media platforms.</p><p> </p><p>Our Police Counter-Terrorism Internet Referral Unit (CTIRU) regularly refers online terrorist and extremist content that breaches social media companies terms and conditions for removal. So far they have secured the removal of over 250,000 pieces of terrorist content since February 2010. CTIRU have developed relationships with over 300 online platforms, and are a YouTube trusted flagger.</p><p> </p><p>The National Crime Agency Child Exploitation and Online Protection Command (CEOP) also has Trusted Flagger status with YouTube, and has similar arrangements with a number of other social media providers.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2017-04-21T14:18:10.02Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715712/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715712/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715712/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-30","Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department is enrolled on any trusted flagger programmes with social media companies.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","70161"
