"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715740","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-18","<p>HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service is considering options to improve its court and tribunal estate in Sunderland. The Courts and Justice Minister Sir Oliver Heald QC wrote to the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland South on 31 March to provide further details.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-04-18T11:26:00.593Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715740/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715740/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715740/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-03-30","Courts: Sunderland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when she plans to update the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland South on plans for the Sunderland courts complex.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","70210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715741","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-04-19","<p>The Northern Ireland Office does not record the number of people from other Government Departments holding security passes who access its premises.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2017-04-19T14:33:52.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715741/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715741/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715741/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-03-30","Northern Ireland Office: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many people holding security passes for other Government Departments are granted access to his Department's premises with that pass, by Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","70070"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715742","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-04-19","<p>As of February 2017, there were 133 staff working in the department; 78 employed directly by the Northern Ireland Office and 50 staff on loan or secondment. In addition, we have five temporary agency workers.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2017-04-19T14:35:07.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715742/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715742/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715742/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-03-30","Northern Ireland Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many people are currently employed by his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","70092"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715743","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-04-20","<p>The Northern Ireland Office (NIO) does not record the total number of security passes it issues and is therefore not able to provide this information. This is as a result of other departments being provided with passes to allow access to their facilities on site outside NIO office hours including access to IT servers.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2017-04-20T11:41:11.737Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715743/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715743/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715743/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-03-30","Northern Ireland Office: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many security passes giving access to his Department's premises have been issued in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","70046"
