"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715012","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-19","<p>All Armed Forces recruits under the age of 18 are enrolled on an apprenticeship. They also receive education in literacy and numeracy, should they need it. The Armed Forces remain the UK's largest apprenticeship provider, equipping young people with valuable and transferable skills for life. OFSTED regularly inspects our care of newly joined young recruits, and we are very proud of the standards we achieve. All apprenticeships require a minimum of 280 Guided Learning Hours (GLHs) within a 12-month period.</p><p>Over 95% of all recruits, no matter what their age or prior qualifications, enrol in an Apprenticeship Programme each year. Apprenticeships ensure that Service personnel will gain a Level 2 qualification in literacy and numeracy, which is the equivalent to GCSE (Grade A-C).</p><p>Since September 2012, the Department has adopted Functional Skills qualifications (FS (English) and FS (mathematics)) as the accredited measures of literacy and numeracy skills for all Service personnel accessing in-Service literacy and numeracy provision. Defence FS provision will be a blend of in-house and external provision.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-04-19T15:56:26.77Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715012/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715012/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715012/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-29","Armed Forces: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what mandatory education is provided to armed forces personnel aged 16 or 17-years old who are not undertaking an apprenticeship in order to ensure that they complete 280 guided learning hours per year towards accredited qualifications.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","69831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715013","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-19","<p>During the recruiting year 2016-17, approximately one per cent of under 18 year-olds who enlisted to the Army were subject to a Care Order.</p><p>For over 18s, from the information held centrally, no enlistees declared that they had been subject to a Care Order*. Thirteen per cent chose not to declare this information.</p><p>*For over 18s, information was available for 89% of enlistees.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-04-19T16:16:20.363Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715013/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715013/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715013/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-29","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of enlisted army recruits aged (a) under and (b) over 18-years old have a background in the care system.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","69832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715014","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-19","<p>This information is not routinely recorded, or held, as part of the recruiting process.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-04-19T15:54:18.127Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715014/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715014/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715014/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-29","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of enlisted soldiers stated on their application form that one or both parents are or were in the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","69833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715015","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-19","<p>Qualification statistics for candidates who entered the Army Foundation College, Harrogate (AFC(H)) in September 2016 are shown below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Entered without</p></td><td><p>Literacy</p></td><td><p>Numeracy</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Level 2 (A*-C)</p></td><td><p>71 %</p></td><td><p>79 %</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Level 1 (D-G)</p></td><td><p>49 %</p></td><td><p>67 %</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>All under 18 enlistees attend AFC(H), except a very small number who will turn 18 before completion of Phase 1 training.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-04-19T15:25:05.06Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715015/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715015/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715015/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-29","Armed Forces: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of soldiers who enlist under 18-years old arrive to train without Level (a) 1 and (b) 2 qualifications in both English and mathematics.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","69834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715016","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-18","<p>Ministry of Defence policies on under-18s in the Armed Forces are robust and comply with national and international law. In addition to the comprehensive welfare system that is in place for all Service personnel we remain fully committed to meeting our obligations under the United Nations Convention on the Rights of the Child, Optional Protocol on the Involvement of Children in Armed Conflict, and have taken steps to bestow special safeguards on young people under the age of 18.</p><p> </p><p>Our recruiting policy is absolutely clear. No one under the age of 18 can join the Armed Forces without formal parental consent, which is checked twice during the application process. In addition, parents and guardians are positively encouraged to be engaged with the recruiting staff during the process. Furthermore all Service personnel have a statutory right to claim discharge up to their 18th birthday, and the right of discharge is made clear to all Service personnel on joining the Armed Forces.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-18T15:29:43.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715016/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715016/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715016/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-29","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he has plans to review the safeguards on consent to enlistment in the light of the Committee on the Rights of the Child's finding in 2016 that such safeguards were insufficient.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","69858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715017","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Department continues to refine plans and costings for the integration of Battlefield Helicopters into the Queen Elizabeth Class Aircraft Carriers in line with the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-18T15:30:50.467Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715017/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715017/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715017/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-29","Aircraft Carriers: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 28 March 2017 to Question 68785, what steps he plans to take in response to the finding of the National Audit Office in paragraph 1.12 of its report on Delivering Carrier Strike, published in March 2017, that the commitment to integrate and support battlefield helicopter operations from the Queen Elizabeth Carriers is yet to be fully funded.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","69865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715018","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-18","<p>Defence Equipment and Support is considering the optimum size of the Lightning Project Team as part of its wider Transformation programme. The next phase will be to recruit personnel to meet the resource requirement.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-18T15:32:47.61Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715018/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715018/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715018/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-29","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 31 of the National Audit Office report, Delivering Carrier Strike, published in March 2017, what steps his Department plans to take to ensure that the project team for the Lightning II programme is not under-resourced.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","69866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715019","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-18","<p>HMS QUEEN ELIZABETH will change the way the Royal Navy (RN) operates and this has been planned for accordingly. While there will be challenges through the transition to the new carriers, we are confident the RN will be able to meet its operational commitments.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-18T15:30:17.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715019/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715019/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715019/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-29","Merlin Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 28 March 2017 to Question 68695, if he has made an assessment of the implications for the availability of Merlin helicopters for the future mainline task group of the findings of the National Audit Office at paragraph 1.9 of its report on Delivering Carrier Strike, published in March 2017.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","69867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715020","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Wildcat tactical data link study contains information related to Armed Forces potential future capability. It therefore cannot be published as this would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-18T15:32:10.323Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715020/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715020/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715020/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-29","Wildcat Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 28 March 2017 to Question 68787, if he will place the feasibility study on the tactical data link for the Wildcat helicopter in the Library.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","69880"
